article.headline: Sacramento St. 71, Cal Poly-SLO 67
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- Sultan Toles-Bey scored 16 points to lead four Sacramento State players in double digits as part of a 71-67 victory over Cal Poly-San Luis Obispo on Saturday night. Jackson Carbajal, Duro Bjegovic and John Dickson helped out with 13 points each. The Hornets (2-3) never led by more than five points despite shooting 59.5 percent from the field. They took the lead for good with about five and a half minutes left, just managing to hold off the Mustangs (2-3), who closed the gap to within a point twice down the stretch. Cal Poly's David Hanson led the game in scoring with 23 points while Shawn Lewis added 14 and Chris O'Brien 12. The Mustang's Will Donahue led the game in rebounds with 10. Cal Poly shot 41.8 percent from the field but outrebounded the Hornets 29-25.
